--- !u!1001 &124643399
PrefabInstance:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  serializedVersion: 2
  m_Modification:
    serializedVersion: 3
    m_TransformParent: {fileID: 0}
    m_Modifications:
    - target: {fileID: 3406898395983688105, guid: b6ff7e9fa6be6224db075a4f94c206ec, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_Name
      value: 'Mission Log #1: Arrival'
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 3435467237574143893, guid: b6ff7e9fa6be6224db075a4f94c206ec, type: 3}
      propertyPath: journalTitle
      value: 'Mission Log #1: Arrival'
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 3435467237574143893, guid: b6ff7e9fa6be6224db075a4f94c206ec, type: 3}
      propertyPath: journalFullText
      value: It is the year 2100. The world's greatest minds could not foresee it,
        but the Earth is beginning to fall into ruin as a terrible calamity approaches.
        The harmful pollution us humans have been releasing into the environment
        has begun to inexplicably grow and spread out of control. Pestilence and
        decay has been destroying more and more of nature, and the government has
        just tasked agents such as myself to look for a solution in a last-ditch
        effort. I was given a mission to investigate this region, in search of a
        natural seed pod that is immune to the calamity through a hypothesized rare
        genetic variation. It's a long shot, but if I can find one, scientists back
        at the city may be able to cultivate it and reproduce it, to plant them back
        in the wild and restore the environment. Strangely enough, while most life
        forms have been suffering due to the calamity, there is one kind of organism
        that has been seen in much larger sizes and population than ever before.
        This organism is called a slime mold. This yellow, slime-like creature has
        been seen practically everywhere. They feed on decaying organic matter, which
        there has been an abundance of due to the calamity, so this must be why they
        have grown so big and common. They also are known to thrive in moist environments.
        There are the roots of dead trees in my way. Perhaps if I get them wet, the
        slime mold may be able to decompose them and break them down, helping me
        get through. I could use the water shooter tool I was supplied with, or if
        there are any other water sources in the area, I may be able to use those
        as well. If there is any brittle stone in my way, I could use my grenades
        to break them apart. They won't work on anything sturdier, though. I was
        also given a fan tool, but I'm not sure yet what it might be useful for.
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 6485533160007763511, guid: b6ff7e9fa6be6224db075a4f94c206ec, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_LocalPosition.x
      value: 1.23
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 6485533160007763511, guid: b6ff7e9fa6be6224db075a4f94c206ec, type: 3}
